Jackson deserialization can be extremely dangerous when handling untrusted input, especially if you enable polymorphic type handling. Multiple critical CVEs (CVE-2019-12384, CVE-2020-35490, CVE-2021-20190) have affected Jackson-databind, allowing attackers to execute arbitrary code.

**VULNERABLE CODE**:

